# Firebase Configuration (for shareable links and hosting)
# Create a Firebase project at https://console.firebase.google.com/
# Free tier includes: 5GB storage, 1GB/day downloads, Firebase Hosting

# Firebase Web App Configuration
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your_project.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your_project.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_sender_id
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_app_id
VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=your_measurement_id

# Instructions:
# 1. Create a new project at https://console.firebase.google.com/
# 2. Enable Storage: Go to Build → Storage → Get Started
# 3. Add a web app: Project Settings → Your apps → Add app (Web)
# 4. Copy the firebaseConfig values from the setup screen
# 5. Create a `.env.local` file in the project root (this file will be ignored by git)
# 6. Copy this template to `.env.local` and replace the placeholder values
# 7. Restart the dev server (npm run dev)
#
# Security note: Firebase config is designed to be public and safe to expose in client code.
# Security is enforced via Firebase Storage security rules (upload-only, file size limits).
